cular innovations, classroom techniques, and advances in assessment to create better learning environments for their students.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aCollege teaching. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Sociology / General.2bisacsh  abackward design.  aco teaching.  acommunity colleges.  acultivating engagement.  acurricular innovations.  afaculty professional development.  afaculty.  afour year institutions.  agraduate students.  ainterests of faculty.  alearning and leadership.  alearning.  anon traditional students.  aonline learning environments.  aprofessors.  aresearch intensive universities.  arubrics.  ascience of learning.  asocial science.  ateaching.1 aAlbert, Craig Douglas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChin, Jeffrey, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChin, Jeffrey, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aHaley-Mize, Shannon, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHoward, Jay R., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHunt, Andrea N., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aIsserles, Robin G., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJackson, Shirley A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKenyon, Kristy, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKirby, Brenda J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKozimor-King, Michele Lee, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKozimor-King, Michele Lee, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aMessineo, Melinda, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMonson, Renee,